<br>
It had been years now since she gave birth to Tolanas, and years more before Kaeltius. Tolanas was named after her father, a warrior Feir'Dal. Kaeltius was named after Maeltreus's grandfather, also a warrior. When they were born the parents could see something very special within them.<br>
<br>
However, Sarah became very worried one night when Tunare sent her dreams that seemed too real, too frightning. She saw herself and Maeltreus, blood poured from them, wounds all over. The blood retreated however, and they both seemed fine, but to her horror she saw their children dead. She knew this was more than what it seemed... it was a vision of the future.<br>
<br>
Every night she kept it secret from Maeltreus, as not to worry him. Also when she woke from the dream she prayed to Tunare to keep her chidren safe. One day, that call was answered, however not to her liking.<br>
<br>
&quot;My dear young druidess... You must have known tragidy was not far ahead when you became involved with him.&quot;<br>
<br>
She started to cry at the joy of just even hearing her goddess's voice.<br>
&quot;I know... I know Tunare but... I just wanted this so badly.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I know... however... the future brings dark tidings. There will come a time when you must make a choice, them... or you. You will know when, I cannot stop it I am sorry to say. I can ensure their safety, however.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Please... do so Tunare.&quot; She pleaded with all of her soul.<br>
<br>
&quot;No... I can but won't. These children are cursed, one is destined to become a greater commander than any to walk this world before. The other will be at his side, a tactician of the best quality. I will not save them.&quot;<br>
<br>
Sarah stood up, her rage building so much a storm brewed around her.<br>
<br>
&quot;DAMN YOU TUNARE! HOW COULD YOU?!? AFTER SO MANY YEARS OF LOYALTY TO YOU AND YOU ALONE AND YOU DENY ME THE SIMPLE RIGHT OF KEEPING MY BELOVED CHILDREN SAFE? YOU ARE NOT THE GODDESS WE THOUGHT YOU TO BE! YOU ARE A FAKE!&quot;<br>
<br>
However, with saying these words she regretted them. Because she was so close to Tunare she felt the pain that Tunare felt with those words.<br>
<br>
&quot;...Very well child...I will help protect them... I will give each a gift. For Tolanas I give the gift of spirit sight. The ability to look into one's soul and know their potential, and who they truly are. For Kaeltius...&quot; She paused.<br>
<br>
&quot;Kaeltius... seems to have his own, from you two... I do not see how but... nevermind, just know he is protected.&quot;<br>
<br>
Sarah breathed a sigh of relief. &quot;Thank you ,Tunare... Thank you.&quot;<br>
<br>
However.. another was listening to them. Innoruuk was furious that a follower so great could be so weak. And now his children might sway to the lightbringers. He would have none of that.<br>
<br>
&quot;I will give them gifts as well Tunare, ones to keep them with me. Tolanas will be the great commander he was supposed to be, for I will personally council him and give him to ability to speak with the gods directly at any time. Kaeltius will be the master tactician for I will give him the ability to see into any opponents weakness instantly by just glancing at them! May these children bring my fury across Norrath!&quot;<br>
<br>
A last one was listening to them all, they did not know though.<br>
He merly laughed at the situation.<br>
&quot;Give them your gifts pitiful ones, I will be able to reach them soon enough. Then I will use yours and give them my own, they will be great. But not for you, for me, they will be great for me or they will die. My time is comming, I will return soon and destroy you all for what you did.&quot;<br>
<br>
10 years later...<br>
<br>
Maeltreus and Sarah were almost out of breath, running frantically as fast as they could. Kaeltius now grown a bit was still very young and could not run as fast on his own so Sarah had elected to carry him. Tolanas tried his best to keep up but in the end Maeltreus had to carry him along as well.<br>
<br>
&quot;Why?! Why cant they just leave us alone!?! We are none of their buisness!!&quot; Sarah shouted through tears.<br>
<br>
More arrows wizzed past their heads and struck the ground of Butcherblock. Teir'Dal swarmed all over, firing arrows and greading their swords. Maeltreus knew them quite well, he knew they would not give up and that him and his wife would sooner fall over in exhaustion then loosing them. He had only one choice left.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sarah! Come here!&quot; He yelled at her as he stopped.<br>
<br>
&quot;What Maeltreus? We must keep moving!&quot;<br>
<br>
Maeltreus looked down at Tolanas, who was now clinging to his fathers plate armor for his life.<br>
&quot;Tolanas, my son... Can you run now? just a little further I promise you.&quot;<br>
<br>
Tolanas nodded quickly and hoped to the ground.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sarah... Take Tolanas and Kaeltius and leave here now! I will hold them until you are far enough to lose them.&quot;<br>
<br>
She looked frantic now, she yelled back at him. &quot;I won't leave you here! You are a part of me Maeltreus! If you die I do as well!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Not today Sarah, you will live on... for our childrens sake. I know your strong Sarah, be so for them if not for yourself. NOW GO!&quot;<br>
<br>
She reluctantly nodded, tears flowing down her cheeks. She took Tolanas's hand and ran off to Greater Faydark, hoping that the Koada'Dal would bring them protection.<br>
<br>
Three elite's from the Indigo brotherhood now stood before him.<br>
&quot;It is no use, we will find her and kill her and your children.&quot;<br>
<br>
Maeltreus never responded he charged them full force and stabbed the one who was talking in his stomech. His deathblow however caught Maeltreus on the shoulder. Another sword went into his side but he would not fall. He swung his blade cutting into the other. The third warrior raised his blade high but Maeltreus cut across his stomech, spilling his organs to the ground.<br>
<br>
He looked at his side where the sword peirced him, the armor stopped most of it so it only went in a little, but enough to hinder him. He was thankful he made side plates that day, encumbering as they were they just saved his life. But the fight was not over.<br>
<br>
Five more ran at him, he knew he would die here but he wouldn't give up. An arrow landed into an opening in his armor just behind his knee. He fell down on it as soon as the arrow struck. The first warrior had already decended on him, Maeltrus acted quickly swinging his sword up and into the warrior.<br>
<br>
Thunk! Another arrow landed into the opening behind the elbow, rendering that arm useless by severing the tendants.<br>
His other arm got cut off by the next warrior. Maeltreus looked up into his eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;My children... will one day rise above you... and kill you all like the scum you are....&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Hardly likely&quot; One said, then he swung down, decapitating Maeltreus.<br>
<br>
Sarah stoped dead in her tracks, just before reaching Felwithe.<br>
<br>
&quot;He's....gone...&quot; She said as a tear slid down her cheek.<br>
<br>
She walked up to the entrance to the city and talked to the guards.<br>
&quot;Please... you must help us, Teir'Dal are comming to kill me and my children.&quot;<br>
<br>
The guard looked at her &quot;Don't worry, your safe here, they wont get past us. We will call fo-&quot; He stopped as he saw Tolanas peek out from behind her leg.<br>
<br>
&quot;Abomination!! We wont protect such things!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What?!!? They may be half Teir'Dal but they are still MY children! you must help!&quot;<br>
<br>
The guard took out his sword &quot;And how do I know your not a spy using these children as a ploy?! I should kill you now to be safe and them to prevent future burdens.&quot;<br>
<br>
She was dazed now, confused as to what was happening. She had gone completely numb, she only knew one thing now. Everyone was against her and her children.<br>
<br>
&quot;YOU WON'T HURT MY BABIES! STARFIRE!&quot;<br>
<br>
He was blasted back into the other guard, dead on impact.<br>
She launched another into the second guard and ran off to lesser faydark. Tolanas looked up at her &quot;Mother pleeeeaaase, can we stop running now? I'm tired!&quot;<br>
<br>
She did not even look down to him &quot;No Tolly I'm sorry... we are going to be running for a very very long time now.&quot;<br>
<br>
5 Years later...<br>
<br>
She had been able to avoid them for years, killing off Teir'Dal and Feir'Dal who had wandered away from their camp trying to find them. Every so often she would find a camp inhabited by one or the other, either looking for her. She would kill all of them, no exceptions. After moving away all the carnage she would bring her children from hiding and take their rations for noureshment and use their camp for cover or safety.<br>
<br>
Today more than ever were in the woods, and they spotted her quickly. Bows flew past her by the second, it was a wonder how they did not even hit her. She found a large tree and hid behind it.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh... Tolanas, why cant they just leave us in peace? we wouldnt harm them if they just left us alone!&quot;<br>
<br>
A Teir'Dal rogue landed beside them from the tree and dove for her with a dagger in hand. <br>
<br>
&quot;STARFIRE!&quot; <br>
<br>
He was dead. She looked around, panicking when another arrow hit the ground beside her. <br>
<br>
&quot;Run Tolanas... Take your brother and run!&quot;<br>
<br>
Tolanas stood defiantly and shook his head. &quot;I won't leave you mother!&quot;<br>
<br>
She placed her hand on each side of his shoulders.<br>
<br>
&quot;Tolanas... I have been using my powers to just keep us alive for so long now, I havent had enough to transport us anywhere else for a long time... I am exhausted and have no power left... You must run Tolanas, run away now with your brother. It's the only chance we have left!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Not quite.&quot; She heard from the tree above.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh no! They found us!&quot;<br>
<br>
The Teir'Dal man jumped off the highest limb like a cat and landed softly to the ground. &quot;No. I am not one of them, but I can help you... at a price.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;How? how can you help us?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I can, trust me.&quot;<br>
<br>
She was reluctant, looking around as if another option was in front of her.<br>
<br>
&quot;You don't have much of a choice... either be helped... or die. I can ensure your children reach Neriak safetly and are well taken care of there. But like I said there is a price.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Anything.&quot; She said exhausted.<br>
<br>
