<br>
&quot;I know Kaeltius.&quot; He put his hand on his brothers shoulder. He could see the anguish and pain in his brothers soul.<br>
<br>
&quot;I miss them alot to... but they are watching over us now.&quot;<br>
<br>
He couldn't bear to tell him the truth, that he had just found out what happened to their mother. That she was stripped of her soul and her body tainted by the blood of a vampire, one who calls himself Mayong Mistmoore. The price she paid was too great, had he known, Tolanas would have thrown himself into the fray just so she wouldnt have to suffer.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well... I guess our father... I am kind of ashamed to even call her my mother. Imagine, our mother... a druid&quot; He said in a disgusted tone.<br>
<br>
&quot;I guess she gets some credit seeing as how she gave us birth.&quot;<br>
<br>
Tolanas narrowed his eyes oin his brother. &quot;No matter who she is you NEVER talk about her like that! She is still our mother damnit!&quot;<br>
<br>
Kaeltius was a bit drunk at the time, Tolanas never liked it but with the harshe training Kaeltius had to endure at the lodge of the dead he thought it alright.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ya ya i know... But all she did was cower there... that other man saved us.&quot;<br>
<br>
Tolanas had enough of this, he could not hear this anymore.<br>
&quot;COMON! You're comming with me NOW!&quot; He yanked his brother out from his seat and dragged him to his horse.<br>
<br>
&quot;Tolanas! where are we going?&quot;<br>
<br>
Tolanas only said one word &quot;Mistmoore.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
When they arrived many ghouls looked upon them with disdain. They could smell their blood though, and knew they were HER children.<br>
<br>
&quot;Don't attack you fools! She will kill us if we kill them!&quot;<br>
<br>
Tolanas didn't even bother to converse with them, he marched past them and straight to the castle, Kaeltius follwing behind.<br>
<br>
When he reached the gates he glowered at the vampires beyond.<br>
&quot;Open the gates now so we may see our mother or I will break them down.&quot; He reached back and grabbed a sword... his fathers sword. The argent protector. It wasent different, it was the exact same one, the initials M.S. were carved into it. Maeltreus Shadowblade.<br>
<br>
The gates lifted and he motioned for his brother to follow. His brother looked nerveously about.<br>
<br>
&quot;Tolanas! The walls, they move!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Calm yourself it is only the ghouls watching us.&quot;<br>
<br>
They were instructed to wait in the main hall. As they did Kaeltius turned to his brother.<br>
<br>
&quot;Tolanas? Why did we come here?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Our mother is here Kaeltius.&quot;<br>
<br>
His blood ran cold when he heard that. He felt like ice as the chills ran down his spine. He looked at his brother, his gold eyes looking as if they were pleading with Tolanas to take what he said back.<br>
<br>
&quot;O-O-Only... vampire's and undead live here... Tolanas... isnt that right?&quot;<br>
<br>
Tolanas nodded. <br>
<br>
&quot;But.. you said our mother was dead!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;For all technical reasons Kaeltius... She is.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Not entirely. I only was reborn my dear son, it does me very well to see you here. I am very happy to see how much my two babies have grown.&quot; She walked down the steps, her chestnut colored hair seemed to flow with a life of its own as she walked. Her eye's no longer held the beutiful gold they held before. They were dull and grey, and though she looked youthful, to Tolanas she was more disgusting than anyone he could ever imagine.<br>
<br>
&quot;Reborn? Don't you need a soul to do that? Last time I checked you have none.&quot; Tolanas said sternly.<br>
<br>
Kaeltius could not believe what he was hearing. His mother lost her soul?! It had to be immpossible!<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh dear... My darling baby... I have not lost it, merly placed it aside.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Spare me the humor you crazed lunatic. Last time we met you tried to make me like you. You are not our mother just a remnant, a burden hanging around where it is'nt wanted.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I am sorry you feel that way... You will have to die then. Kaeltius!&quot; She smiled as she looked at him. She walked up to him and hugged him.<br>
<br>
&quot;It's been so long, you won't be like your brother right? You will join us won't you?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Mother... I can't believe.... this is what you gave for us..&quot;<br>
<br>
Tears spilled from his eye's as he remembered everything he had said through his lifetime about her. He hugged her back.<br>
<br>
&quot;I am so sorry mother! If only I had known what happened!... I .... I could not be more proud to have had a mother like you... I am such an ingrate, an ungrateful poor excuse of a son.. I'm so sorry.&quot;<br>
<br>
She looked at Tolanas and grinned evilly.<br>
<br>
&quot;You can make it up to me you know.... Join me and live the rest of your days here... I can forgive you.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I... I wasent talking to you!&quot; He shouted much to her surprise.<br>
&quot;I was talking to my real mothers soul!!&quot;<br>
<br>
She saw he was going to back away. She opened her mouth and was about to drive her fangs into his throat.<br>
<br>
Tolanas's eyes shot open &quot;NO! KAELTIUS!&quot;<br>
<br>
Then... she stopped. She unfolded her arms from him, shaking she backed up and looked down at her stomech. An enchanted dagger had embedded itself there.<br>
<br>
&quot;May you be damned to an eternal torment. We will release her soul by destroying you!&quot; Kaeltius said in a rage.<br>
&quot;Innoruuk!!! Goive me the strength to battle this thing!&quot;<br>
<br>
He charged forward unknowing a vampire's attributes. She quickly pulled the dagger from her stomech and was ready to stab him, but she noticed a shadow engulfing hers. As she turned around the last thing she saw was the Argent protecter slicing into her neck. Quickly the body turned to dust.<br>
<br>
&quot;May your soul be set free mother.&quot; Tolanas turned to his brother. &quot;It's done... and now you know what she sacrificed to save us. No more badmouthing her got it? you do it again and you get a ticket to the emergency section in the clerics temple of Innoruuk.&quot;<br>
<br>
Kaeltius could only nod. To shaken by the events to do anything else. Tolanas had already been through the shock to be shocked again.<br>
<br>
Tolanas pulled a small sack out and shoved their mother's remains inside. He took out a small bottle and handed it to Kaeltius.<br>
<br>
&quot;Time to go back home, drink this.&quot; Kaeltius did as he was instructed and dissapeared.<br>
<br>
&quot;Too bad I only had one.&quot; Tolanas said as he heard the angry screams of the undead around him. They clawed at the walls and doors breaking them down. Tolanas knew the futility of fighting them back, but was going to make them work for their next meal. Slowly he raised his sword, waiting for them to come after him.<br>
<br>
The noises rose more and more, they were striking the doors harder.... no.... it wasent the doors he heard. It was someone else fighting them. He was surprised when he saw his old friend, the one who used to be second in command in his army. Priestess Llandra now the commander of his old army stalked him and smiled. &quot;Happy to see me Tolanas?&quot;<br>
<br>
