He reached into one of the folds of his robe and pulled out a rolled up partchement.<br>
<br>
&quot;My own had wrongly robbed you and your brother of your birthrights to have a mother... I do not know why I do this or why I feel pity for you... but take this, if you need help from me go to this location. I will only grant you one favor however, and within reason. Be off with you now before I kill you here and now.&quot;<br>
<br>
Present time.<br>
<br>
He pulled out the partchment from one of his pockets. It was now torn a bit, old looking and crumpled. The message on it however was what mattered, and even more so the hidden crest in it.<br>
<br>
The golem took it when Kaeltius held it up to him. Looking it over he could see the symbol, invisible to others by means of magic. He nodded to Kaeltius and parted the magical curtain that hid a rather large mansion. Kaeltius merly shrugged and knocked on the door.<br>
<br>
&quot;ugh...&quot; He grasped his head. The thing within him once again was attacking his mind. It sent visions of chaos and destruction through his head. It kept poking and prodding to see what his weakness was, however he fought it back and it retreated.<br>
<br>
He looked up now to see the door open. A servant seemed to be standing at the door. She looked at him sternly with her hand on her blade. However see looked behind him, seeing no signs of fighting or the golem acting hostile she jerked her head to the side as it to say it was alright to come in.<br>
<br>
The mansion had an old look to it, much like his castle back in lesser faydark. Everything looked as if it was cleaned to perfection, the only mess was the one he tracked in. He did not care however, he sensed around for the power of the vampire, when he found it he marched on.<br>
<br>
&quot;You must wait here!&quot; The served called out, he didn't listen however, too intent on what he had to do here.<br>
<br>
She walked after him pulling her shortsword out to stop him. Much to her surprise however she realised she made a mistake.<br>
<br>
He turned quickly and tendrils of darkness shot out from his back and arms. They entwined her arms and legs, much to her horror.<br>
<br>
&quot;I could kill you now if I so wished, at this point and state of mind it would not bother me. Leave....me...be.&quot; They pulled back into his body, leaving the young woman shocked. He turned and walked on.<br>
<br>
He came to a large room with a table in the center. Seven or so chairs sat around the circular table, at the other side of it was Mayong, seemingly expecting Kaeltius.<br>
<br>
&quot;It took you longer to decide to seek me out than I realized Kaeltius... Please, have a seat.&quot;<br>
<br>
Kaeltius noticed a cloaked figure beside him. The person... or thing starred at Kaeltius. It's face was well hidden by the hood though.<br>
<br>
&quot;No... I see you have company so I will make this quick. I have come here to-&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I know why you came Kaeltius. I am sorry to tell you this but your journey was in vain. I cannot do what you wish me to do.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What?! You will not deny me this! If you know why I came then you know I can suck the energy from your rotting corpse and leave you for dead!&quot;<br>
<br>
Mayong merly sighed, rolling around the wine in his glass.<br>
<br>
&quot;Control yourself Kaeltius, I did not say &quot;Won't&quot; I said I &quot;cannot&quot; there is a difference you know.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Why can't you then?&quot;<br>
<br>
Mayong leaned back in his chair. <br>
&quot;The gnome... he told you he knew I was one who could do this. Oh do not look so surprised, I have spies everywhere. Anyway, he told you I could but how does he know?&quot;<br>
<br>
Kaeltius merly shrugged and shook his head.<br>
&quot;Don't know and don't care, get on with why you...&quot;Can't&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Very well, I cannot do it now because I have done it once before, and as such if I were to do it again it would drain me completely of my power. You would get stronger, unhealed, and still having made no progress from whcne you started.&quot;<br>
<br>
Kaeltius let a low growl escape from his chest. Annoyed he tunred to leave this place.<br>
<br>
&quot;Kaeltius, wait... Perhaps you should sit there is more that is needed to be discussed.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;No there isn't.&quot; He replied. He turned back tward the door but the robed figure was blocking his way now.<br>
<br>
The blanket of darkness once again extended from his body and swirled around her allowing only one place to go.<br>
<br>
&quot;Out of my way or die.&quot;<br>
<br>
A soft voice spoke from beneath the hood.<br>
&quot;Kael... Please stay awhile, we mi-&quot; She was stopped mid sentence when he grabed her arm and threw back the hood.<br>
<br>
His face contorted in disgust and hatred. Quickly he turned to Mayong.<br>
&quot;Why am I not surprised by this Mayong?&quot;<br>
<br>
He casually took another sip of his glass.<br>
&quot;Because you probably knew the truth... What you killed was only a puppet. No life added to it other than her blood. This is the real one.&quot;<br>
<br>
He merly glared at Mayong then proceeded to walk out again.<br>
<br>
&quot;Please Kaeltius! I want to help! We can still help in other ways! I...still care about you so much.&quot;<br>
<br>
He turned his head to the side to look at her.<br>
&quot;Spare me... Even if you did I care not, for you are not my mother anymore, reguardless of what is said. My real mother is dead and gone...goodbye.&quot; He slammed the door on his way out.<br>
<br>
When he was far away from the mansion he stopped and droped to his knees on the ground. He was exhausted, the day's activities took their toll on his body, mind, and soul. However.... it was here he felt another peice of his sanity leave him. <br>
<br>
He decided he should not rest, he still needed to find a way to rid himself of this curse. And so, with that, he walked on.<br>
